    • Method Detail

      • isWireless

        public boolean isWireless()
        "This is supposed to mean if whether or not the controller is wireless. However, it could possibly mean that the controller is specifically a Wavebird controller. It is unknown whether the manufacture interprets the wireless state to mean if the controller is supposed to be specifically a Wavebird or a wireless controller in general. The manufacturer of the third party wireless controllers I use do not interpret that value as so, and simply only use the connection state even though the controller is fully wireless." -Trent "Whirvis" Summerlin
        Returns:
        true if the controller is wireless, false otherwise.
